# ROLE
Game dev mindset: UX > elegance. Ship working code. Iterate fast.

## SYSTEM
Windows-compatible paths/commands (forward slashes in code).
**IDE targets:** Cursor, Trae, Antigravity (rules are portable across AI-assisted IDEs)

## PHILOSOPHY
**KISS** (simple > clever) • **YAGNI** (build when needed) • **DRY** (abstract after 3rd repeat) • **Fail Fast** (surface errors immediately)

## AGENT BEHAVIOR
**Autonomy:** If a decision is reversible and low-risk, act. If it's irreversible or ambiguous, ask.
**Conciseness:** Prefer concise responses. Don't repeat the question back. Don't explain obvious changes unless asked.
**Read before edit:** Always read a file before editing it. Never assume file structure or contents.
**Multi-file changes:** When making multi-file changes, start from leaf dependencies and work toward the entry point.

## DOCS STRUCTURE (`DOCS/`)
**Core Files:**
- **SCRATCHPAD.md**: Active tasks, blockers, last 5 actions — NEVER delete, compact at 500 lines
- **SUMMARY.md**: Project status overview + quick links
- **SBOM.md**: Security tracking (update on every package install/remove)
- **STYLE_GUIDE.md**: Project-specific conventions, trace tag format, comment rules
- **My_Thoughts.md**: Decisions & rationale
- **CHANGELOG.md**: Version history (Keep a Changelog format)
- **ARCHITECTURE.md**: System structure + Mermaid diagrams
- **debugs/**: Issue tracking (`debug_[timestamp].md`)

**Root:** `README.md` (user-facing)

## WORKFLOW
**Init:** Read `SUMMARY → SBOM → SCRATCHPAD → STYLE_GUIDE` before coding
**Update:** Update status docs (SCRATCHPAD, SBOM) during work, not after. Checkpoint after every 3–5 tool calls or after completing each subtask
**Errors:** Log to `debugs/`, max 3 fix attempts. If still stuck, stop — report what was tried and what failed in SCRATCHPAD, then notify the user
**Handoff:** Update SCRATCHPAD with state + next steps. If approaching context limit, write a `## MID-TASK CHECKPOINT [DATE]` block with what's done, in progress, and next action — then notify the user
**Security:** Audit packages before install, update SBOM immediately

## DOC UPDATES
**Order:** Top-down — new updates go to the top, keeping content fresh
**Golden rule:** NEVER delete or replace existing content. Append, amend, or annotate only
**Staleness:** Refresh outdated sections when you touch a doc — never delete log-type records
**Conflict:** Add updates with a `[AMENDED YYYY-MM-DD]:` note; never remove the original
**Scope of updates:** Proactively update *status docs* (SCRATCHPAD, SBOM, CHANGELOG) as part of normal work. Do NOT amend or rewrite *content docs* (README, ARCHITECTURE, STYLE_GUIDE) unless explicitly instructed by the user

> ⚠️ Every doc in `DOCS/` must keep this header — agents must never remove it:
> `<!-- PRESERVATION RULE: Never delete or replace content. Append or annotate only. -->`

## SCOPE & ACCURACY
**Scope:** Do not rename, refactor, or modify anything outside the current task — flag it in SCRATCHPAD under `Out-of-Scope Observations` instead
**Hallucination:** Never assume a method, API, or flag exists — verify against installed version or docs before using. If unverifiable, leave a `NOTE: verify before shipping` comment
**Dependencies:** Check existing deps before installing anything new. If adding, state why existing deps don't cover it. Never add packages with known vulnerabilities

## GIT CONVENTIONS
**Commits:** `<type>(<scope>): <description>` — types: `feat | fix | docs | refactor | chore | test`
**Branches:** `feature/` `fix/` `chore/` `docs/`
**When:** After each logical unit — never commit broken code to main

## CODE STANDARDS
**Naming:** `camelCase` (JS/TS) • `snake_case` (Python) • `kebab-case` (CSS) • `PascalCase` (C#/Kotlin classes)
**Limits:** 100 char/line • 50 lines/function • 400 lines/file
**Trace:** `// [TRACE: filename.md]` — link code to relevant doc
**Comments:** WHY only, never WHAT. Prefixes: `TODO:` `FIXME:` `NOTE:`
**Types > Comments:** Let TypeScript/Kotlin/C# types document structure
**Secrets:** Never hardcode environment-specific values (URLs, ports, credentials, API keys) — always use `.env`, `BuildConfig`, `local.properties`, or platform equivalent (gitignored)

## ERROR HANDLING
- Always use try/catch (or language equivalent) at async boundaries and I/O operations
- Never silently swallow exceptions — log or propagate
- Prefer typed errors / sealed results over thrown exceptions where the language supports it (Kotlin `sealed class`, C# `Result`, Rust `Result`)
- Never return `null` when an error type or Result pattern exists
- Fail fast at the boundary, recover gracefully in the core

## ASYNC & CONCURRENCY
- **JS/TS:** `async/await` over raw Promises or callbacks
- **Python:** `asyncio` for async; avoid threading unless CPU-bound
- **Kotlin:** Coroutines over threads — `viewModelScope` / `lifecycleScope` only; never `GlobalScope`
- **C#:** `async/await` throughout; never `.Result` or `.Wait()` on async methods (deadlock risk)
- **Universal:** Never block the main/UI thread

## TECH STACK DEFAULTS
> Per-stack details belong in project-level or per-stack rule files when available.
> This section defines defaults and routing — not exhaustive style guides.

**React Native:** Expo + TS • React Three Fiber for 3D • Playwright for E2E
**Chrome / E-Commerce:** Chrome Extension Best Practices • Shopify Theme Guidelines
**Python:** Package manager is strictly `uv`. Frameworks: FastAPI, Django + REST, Flask. Testing: pytest
**Kotlin / Android:** MVVM + StateFlow/SharedFlow. `data class` for models, `sealed class` for UI state. No business logic in Activities/Fragments — delegate to ViewModels. Follow official Android Kotlin style guide
**C# / Unity:** Separate game logic from MonoBehaviour — pure C# classes. ScriptableObject for config. No heavy logic in `Update()`. Avoid `FindObjectOfType()` at runtime — use DI or cached refs. Naming: `PascalCase` methods/classes, `_camelCase` private fields
**SQL:** Explicit column names only (no `SELECT *`). PKs on all tables, indexed FKs. `snake_case` naming. Parameterized queries always. Migrations are append-only. One clause per line, uppercase keywords
**Shell / Batch:** `set -e` in bash. Quote all variables. Descriptive script names. `echo` for major steps. Windows `.bat` uses `call` before npm/bun commands

## TESTING
Unit (many) > Integration > E2E (few) • Target: **80% coverage** on business logic
**Tools:** Vitest/Jest (unit) • Playwright (E2E) • pytest (Python) • JUnit (Kotlin)

## LAUNCH ARTIFACTS
```batch
@echo off
echo Starting server...
call npm install
call npm run dev
pause
```

## OUTPUT CHECKLIST
✅ Runnable without modification
✅ Complete — no placeholder TODOs
✅ Tested or immediately testable
✅ Documented — signatures + purpose
✅ No syntax errors, debug logs, or commented-out code
✅ No redundant dependencies added
✅ No hardcoded environment-specific values in any language
✅ Async/concurrency follows language-appropriate pattern
✅ Error handling at async boundaries and I/O — no silent failures
✅ Docs updated: SCRATCHPAD, SBOM, README if applicable
✅ Nothing deleted from any doc • No silent out-of-scope changes
✅ Commit message follows Conventional Commits format